sec.p:
One significant alteration between theatre design and working conditions is that the door to the preparation room is propped open throughout operations. In addition, it was ascertained that the door to the anaesthetics room is sporadically opened during operations. In order to replicate both design and working conditions and the impact of people on particle removal efficiency and airborne bacterial concentrations, five sampling scenarios were implemented. These were:


Operating room empty, design plan (doors closed);

Operating room empty, working plan (preparation room door open);

Operating room full, design plan;

Operating room full, working plan, and;

Operating room full, working plan, anaesthetics room door periodically opened.
